# Documentation Configuration

# This project uses LLMS.txt files for enhanced AI documentation support.

# When available, use @Docs to reference documentation from:

# - Chakra UI: https://chakra-ui.com/llms-full.txt

# - Next.js: Available through next-devtools-mcp

# - NX: Available through nx-mcp

# - Other integrations: Check their respective LLMS.txt files

# MCP Servers Configuration

# MCP servers are configured in .cursor/mcp.json (for Cursor) and .gemini/settings.json (for Gemini CLI)

# Available MCP servers:

# - chakra-ui: Chakra UI component library and design tokens

# - next-devtools: Next.js development tools and runtime access

# - playwright: Browser automation and testing (works with Next.js)

# - nx: Nx monorepo tools and workspace understanding

# - neon: Neon database management (uses OAuth - will prompt for authentication)

# Alternative: Use local API key version by replacing with:

# {"command": "npx", "args": ["-y", "@neondatabase/mcp-server-neon", "start", "<YOUR_NEON_API_KEY>"]}

# - vercel: Vercel deployment and project management (uses OAuth - will prompt for authentication)

# - browser-use: Browser automation capabilities (requires BROWSER_USE_API_KEY environment variable)

# Environment Variables Required

# - BROWSER_USE_API_KEY: Required for browser-use MCP server (get from https://cloud.browser-use.com)

# Note: Replace ${BROWSER_USE_API_KEY} in .cursor/mcp.json and .gemini/settings.json with your actual API key,

# or set it as an environment variable if your MCP client supports environment variable expansion.

# Better Auth MCP

# Note: Better Auth MCP is a plugin that makes your app an OAuth provider for MCP clients,

# not an external MCP server. It is configured separately in your Better Auth setup.

# See: https://www.better-auth.com/docs/plugins/mcp

# For Drizzle ORM integration with Better Auth, see: https://www.better-auth.com/docs/adapters/drizzle

# Documentation References

# Use @Docs to access comprehensive documentation from configured MCP servers.

# Each MCP server provides access to relevant documentation and tools.
